6.02	Anna_Hall_Roosevelt	Anna Hall Roosevelt	Anna Rebecca Livingston Ludlow Hall Roosevelt (March 17, 1863 – December 7, 1892) was the mother of First Lady of the United States, Anna Eleanor Roosevelt. Anna was the eldest child of Valentine Gill Hall (1834–1880) and Mary Livingston Ludlow (1843–1919). She was a descendant of Livingston family, Her siblings were: Elizabeth (1865–1944), Valentine Jr. (1867–1934), Mary (1869–1872), Edward (1872–1932), Edith (1873–1920) and Maude (1877–1952).	
